    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that works for the vibe. to make it feel more authentic to a real urban setting, i want to add some specific ethnic or racial identifiers to the characters. for example, if i wanted to lean into the \"urban decay\" trope, should i describe these groups as mostly black or latino gang members to make the threat feel more \"real\" and stereotypical for the genre? or does that feel too cliché for a modern script?",
